Step - 1
--------

The following debian packages must be installed first:
------------------------------------------------------

libssh2-1_1.2.6-1_amd64.deb       
perl-base_5.20.1-4_amd64.deb  
yuma_2.2-5.tar.gz
haproxy_1.5.9-1_amd64.deb         
libssh2-1-dev_1.2.6-1_amd64.deb          
yuma_2.2-5_amd64.changes      
yuma-dev_2.2-5_all.deb
init-system-helpers_1.22_all.deb  
libxml2_2.7.8.dfsg-2+squeeze8_amd64.deb  
yuma_2.2-5_amd64.deb          
yuma-doc_2.2-5_all.deb
libpcre3_8.35-3.3_amd64.deb       
OpenYuma-master.zip 
yuma_2.2-5.dsc

Step - 2
--------

A folder "modules" has to be created in the home directory which must contain the file "haproxy.yang"

haproxy.yang 
------------

module haproxy{
        namespace "http://netconfcentral.org/ns/haproxy";
    prefix "haproxy";

    revision 2014-12-09 {
        description "Initial revision.";
    }

        container haproxy {
        description
        "configuration parameters for haproxy load balancers";
        container frontend {
                leaf name {
                type string;
                }
                leaf bind{
                type string;
                }
                leaf default_backend {
                type string;
                }

        }
        container backend {
                leaf name {
                type string;
                }
                leaf mode {
                type string;
                }

                leaf balance {
                type string;
                }
                leaf IPAddress {
                type string;
                }
                leaf action {
                type string;
                }

        }

}


Step - 3
--------

Create a <filename>.so file from the "haproxy.yang" data model using Openyuma-Master dev package and place that <filename>.so file in /usr/lib/yuma/

Step - 4
--------

Edit the file /etc/ssh/sshd_config and append these two lines:

Port 830
Subsystem netconf /usr/sbin/netconf-susbsystem

Step - 5
--------

Restart the ssh service using command "sudo service ssh restart"

Step - 6
--------

Add superuser and module in the crontab:

"crontab -u tcs -l; echo "@reboot /usr/sbin/netconfd --module=haproxy --superuser=tcs"  | crontab -u tcs -"
